> What are the futures markets for coffee in Brazil?
**assistant**:
> The futures market for coffee in Brazil is an exchange where coffee producers, traders, roasters and other market participants can buy and sell futures contracts for coffee. These contracts are agreements to buy or sell a specified amount of coffee at a predetermined price on a future date. This market provides a way for participants to hedge against price fluctuations and manage price risk, while also enabling speculators to profit from changes in the price of coffee. The two main futures markets for coffee in Brazil are the Intercontinental Exchange (ICE) and the Bolsa de Valores de São Paulo (B3).
